<header id="detail-header">
	<h1>The King of Kings</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m06.gif" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>The King of Kings</em> is a silent epic film directed by Cecil B. DeMille, starring H.B. Warner, Dorothy Cumming, Ernest Torrence, Joseph Schildkraut, and James Neil.</p>

		<p>Cecil B. DeMille produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by Pathé Exchange on 19 April 1927, with a runtime of 155 minutes.

			
				It had a budget of $1.2 million and made $2.6 million at the box office.
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $20.7 million and $45 million, respectively.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Jeanie MacPherson, with Hugo Riesenfeld and Josiah Zuro composing the film’s music. J. Peverall Marley and F.J. Westerberg oversaw cinematography, and Anne Bauchens and Harold McLernon helped with editing the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="https://archive.org/details/TheKingOfKings1927ByCecilB.DeMille">View an archived version of <em>The King of Kings</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_King_of_Kings_(1927_film)">View the Wikipedia entry for <em>The King of Kings</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="../index.html">Return to the list</a> to select a different film.</p>
	</section>

